&nbsp;
New version released!
&nbsp;
**Changes in v1.3.2**
- Improved site layout
- The site now warns you if your browser is incompatible, generates a link for alternate video player.
- More movies and TV shows coming... stay tuned!
&nbsp;
**Introduction**
&nbsp;
KopyKate is an uncensored YouTube alternative for ZeroNet, which allows you to watch and upload copyrighted content. Works by storing WebTorrent magnetlinks on a decentralized database on a ZeroNet site, and then playing the torrents using a javascript and WebRTC-based torrent client so you don't have to download any extra software!
&nbsp;
That means the site is impossible to shutdown as the magnet link database is hosted by thousands of users all across the world. DMCA raids tend to go after the servers where magnet links are stored.. as you can't exactly outlaw torrent clients, any more than you can outlaw web browsers, or the internet itself.
&nbsp;
You can seed torrents using WebTorrent.Desktop (tutorials available) or you can create webseeds, too. Webseeds are recommended for videos that may not get a lot of views, especially during the early stage of the site. Even watching videos automatically seeds them, so the more viewers the better.
&nbsp;
**A bit about me:**
&nbsp;
I'm a YouTuber and broke college student in IT who is frustrated by the sheer lunacy of copyright laws.. and also the ad-revenue system on YouTube. Long story short - The rise of Adblock has given way to the establishment of YouTube Red - a monthly paid service. So that's YouTube essentially saying - because you suckers aren't willing to put up with annoying and irrelevant ads - we'll force you to pay for using our services! But then, we need YouTube .. just like we need roads, telephones and fresh drinking water.. so that sucks!
&nbsp;
KopyKate will not rely on Ads for revenue, nor does it need them to keep the lights on. You can however get your video featured for a small monthly fee - what that means is your video will have the highest possible ranking in search results. Spammy, annoying videos will not get featured. This will be the only source of revenue, as I don't believe in accepting donations.
&nbsp;
Ultimately though, it's a non-profit kind of project. 20 years from now, we will have a Universal Basic Income, and robots doing all the dirty jobs that nobody wants to do.. so money will not really matter that much because even programmers will one day be replaced by general AI and machine learning. If we ever do make it big, we'll give all the profit to charity, and keep enough to just pay the rent. There's no such thing as a free lunch - unless you get your computer to cook it for you..
&nbsp;
I've had multiple people interested in collaborating, so yeah.. let's do this.. fuck procrastinating. All work will be credited and acknowledged on the Github repository, no matter how small. We need programmers fluent in javascript, but more than an anything - we just need to get people to SEED .. or in other words, get as many people to watch as many videos as possible and upload as much as possible. I've also noticed that a lot of people have struggled using the site at times, even people on ZeroNet - so the goal is to make the site as user-friendly as possible to get as many people to commit massive amounts of copyright infringement with the click of a button, as possible.
&nbsp;
Programmers of the world - Unite! To the bitter end. Because college no longer gets you a good job and because the basic necessities of life should be Free.

