Update: Just done some improvements on the uploader. Videos now play automatically when uploaded using the Torrent upload button. I've also been thinking of implementing a peer-discovery script that prevents videos from showing in search results if they have less than 1 peer. There should be a way to do this without slowing it down.. by pre-loading the database entries, but only displaying them if they have at least 1 peer. The Add Video button also will be grayed out if your uploaded torrent isn't being seeded, so that will also stop un-seeded torrents from making their way to kopykate. ;) 
&nbsp;
It came to my attention that the tracker on Webtorrent.io has stopped working.
Torrent discovery seems to be taking longer as a result. Luckily, WebTorrent uses bittorrent trackers, so I might experiment using trackers from The Pirate Bay.. or even setting up my own tracker. 
&nbsp;
WebRTC-based DHT is yet to be implemented!
